        "tema_cls": null,
        "no_kd": null,
        "pertanyaan": "<p>Gorillas are the largest apes in the world. They are our closest cousins because they share 98.3 percent of their genetic code with humans. Gorillas have broad shoulders and chests, human-like hands, small eyes, and hairless faces. Their nostrils are large. Gorillas have behaviors and also emotions. They can laugh and show their sadness.<\/p><p>Gorillas only live in tropical forests of Africa. We can find gorillas in the rain forests of Cameroon and Congo.<\/p><p>Gorillas are vegetarians. They eat leaves, shoots, and stalks. They also sometimes eat fruits.<\/p><p>Gorillas live in \u2026<\/p>",
